OL,3,CWho is Apple's new CEO John Ternus?
OL,5,F"Having spent almost my entire career
OL,6,Fat Apple, I have been lucky to have
OL,7,Fworked under Steve Jobs and to have
OL,8,Fhad Tim Cook as my mentor. It has been
OL,9,Fa privilege to help shape the products
OL,10,Fand experiences that have changed so
OL,11,Fmuch of how we interact with the world
OL,12,Fand with one another.
OL,14,F"I am filled with optimism about what
OL,15,Fwe can achieve in the years to come,
OL,16,Fand I am so happy to know that the
OL,17,Fmost talented people on earth are here
OL,18,Fat Apple, determined to be part of
OL,19,Fsomething bigger than any one of us."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/13
